@startuml sequence-legacy
title AS-IS: P2P Transfer — Logic Inside Service

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequenceParticipant underline

actor Client
participant "API Gateway\n:8000" as GW #LightBlue
participant "Payment Service\n:8001" as PS #LightYellow
participant "Ledger Mock\n:8003" as LM #LightGreen

note over GW, LM #Pink
  AS-IS PROBLEMS:
  - Decision logic is inside payment-service (if-else code)
  - No audit trail — nobody can answer "which rule matched?"
  - No rule versioning — changing a limit = deploy
  - No rule ownership — who do you call when AML list is wrong?
  - Logic will be duplicated in every service that needs it
end note

Client -> GW: POST /api/p2p/transfer-legacy\nIdempotency-Key: key-001\n{amount: 500000, country: "IR", ...}

GW -> GW: Inject X-Correlation-Id\n(if missing)

GW -> PS: POST /p2p/transfer-legacy\nX-Correlation-Id: corr-abc\nIdempotency-Key: key-001

note over PS #LightYellow
  INLINE DECISION LOGIC (anti-pattern):
  if daily_sum + amount > 10_000_000:
    reject("LIMIT_EXCEEDED")
  elif country in ["IR","KP","CU","SY"]:
    reject("AML_BLOCKED")           ← matches here
  elif device_trust == "LOW" and amount > 200000:
    reject("FRAUD_SUSPECTED")
  else:
    call ledger
end note

PS -> PS: if country == "IR": REJECT ← hardcoded

PS --> GW: 200 {status: "REJECTED",\n  reason: "AML_BLOCKED"}\n  ← no rule_id\n  ← no owner\n  ← no version\n  ← no audit_id

GW --> Client: 200 {status: "REJECTED",\n  reason: "AML_BLOCKED"}

note over Client #Pink
  Client asks: "Which rule blocked it?"
  Answer: "AML_BLOCKED" — a string, not a reference.

  Business asks: "Who owns this rule?"
  Answer: "Check the code."

  Compliance asks: "What version of AML list was active?"
  Answer: "Git blame, good luck."

  Auditor asks: "Show me the decision log for this transaction."
  Answer: "We don't have one."
end note

@enduml
